<TEXT>
the united states is gravely 
concerned that communist north korea may be developing nuclear 
weapons the south korean news agency yonhap reported from 
washington on friday 
it said the state department is keeping a close watch on possible 
efforts in north korea to develop nuclear weapons yonhap quoted 
spencer richardson the head of the departments korea section as 
saying moscow would be as concerned as washington if north korea 
produced such weapons 
secretary of state james baker is expected to discuss north 
koreas nuclear capability with soviet foreign minister eduard 
shevardnadze at a meeting in the united states this month yonhap 
reported 
while denying it has nuclear weapons north korea has repeatedly 
charged that us forces based in south korea are equipped with 
nuclear arms and are preparing for a nuclear war on the divided 
korean peninsula us officials reject the north korean claims 
the united states keeps about 43000 troops in south korea under 
a defense pact the soviet union is the norths main arms supplier 
chances are dim for an improvement soon in the strained relations 
between the united states and north korea despite diplomatic 
contacts between the two sides in beijing the report quoted 
richardson as saying 
north korea demands immediate withdrawal of us troops from 
south korea seoul says us forces are vital to prevent a north 
korean attack 
north korea invaded south korea in 1950 setting off the 3year 
korean war us forces intervened on the side of south korea and 
fought under the united nations banner us troops have remained in 
the south ever since 
