but he said statistics on hispanics are troubling because they 
show onethird of all hispanics aged 16 to 24 were not enrolled in 
school and were not high school graduates last year 
the report dropout rates in the united states 1988 showed 
44 percent of students in grades 10 through 12 dropped out of high 
school annually in the years 19851988 down from 66 percent in 
1978 nearly 13 percent of all 16 to 24yearolds were not in 
school and had not completed school last year down from 16 percent 
in 1968 
