the soviet union today launched two monkeys into 
orbit to enable scientists to study the effects of zero gravity and 
space radiation on living beings tass reported 
on thursday the soviet union used a single rocket to put six 
cosmos satellites into orbit the series numbered 2038 through 
2043 were hurled into space by a tsiklon booster rocket tass said 
today 
the monkeys space capsule home which will be in orbit for the 
next two weeks was launched by a soyuz booster rocket the official 
news agency said 
tass said the experiment is part of a program organized by 
scientists from the united states canada france hungary east 
germany poland romania czechoslovakia and the european space 
agency 
after the flights program is fulfilled the biological 
specimens and scientific equipment will be returned to earth for 
further studies tass said 
in october 1987 the soviet union carried out space experiments 
with two monkeys who quickly captured the public imagination with 
their antics aboard the spacecraft beamed back to earth by 
television cameras 
one of the monkeys named yerosha broke free and appeared to 
viewers with a free left front paw and without his nametag on his 
helmet the mission was almost aborted when scientists learned he 
had blocked his food tube 
tass said of thursdays launch apart from scientific 
instrumentation the satellites have radio systems for precise 
measuring of orbital elements and radio systems to transmit data to 
earth on the operation of instruments and scientific equipment 
two soviet cosmonauts meanwhile were busy assembling and 
reactivating research equipment aboard the mir space station which 
had been mothballed for four months before they arrived on sept 5 
the news agency said 
cosmonauts alexander viktorenko and alexander serebrov on 
wednesday used the propulsion unit of their spaceship to change the 
orbit of the mir orbiter tass said 
it said they also had replaced components of the lifesupport 
systems and completed preparations for an experiment to produce 
highquality semiconductor materials in the gravityfree environment 
the cosmonauts are feeling fine tass said adding that they 
would take the weekend off to relax 
the 20ton spacecraft was designed to be permanently manned and 
two cosmonauts last year set a record by staying in space for a year 
but mir was unexpectedly unmanned in april because two addon 
modules were not ready the space agency also was under pressure 
from legislators and citizens who felt its funds could be better 
spent at home 
the fourmonth vacancy was only the second time that mir was 
unmanned since it was launched in february 1986 
