was a bit tense 
obviously they are frightened by this new reality i 
believe some of the policemen were shocked they have been told not 
to allow this and they dont understand when they are told not to 
take action he said 
when chikane emerged from the station he and storey climbed a 
ladder to speak to the crowd from a concrete ledge and told the 
marchers to disperse telling them we have proved our point 
the crowd joined storey in a prayer sang god bless africa 
the anthem of the antiapartheid movement and dispersed 
several thousand youths jogged and chanted anc slogans on their 
way to bus and train stations to return home 
