the plan approved by the committee would reduce the tax rate of 
33 percent to 196 percent for the next 27 months the tax rate then 
would rise to 28 percent but would be indexed to tax only 
increases exceeding the annual inflation rate 
the net effect to taxpayers is similar to bushs campaign 
proposal to reduce the capital gains tax rate to 15 percent without 
indexing 
the ways and means budget bill also lowers the premiums for 
catastrophic health insurance for the elderly and finances a massive 
increase in childcare subsidies for lowincome families the 1990 
