<TEXT>
the night stalker jurys deliberations 
were interrupted friday by a jurors illness but the panel planned 
to resume for a 20th day monday 
the jury which had to restart deliberations after one panelists 
death began its talks anew on aug 16 
eleven of the 12 jurors started discussing the case july 26 
their first 13 days of deliberations were ordered scrapped when a 
juror died and an alternate was substituted 
on aug 14 the initial deliberations were interrupted by word 
that juror phyllis singletary was found beaten and shot at her home 
her livein boyfriend later committed suicide and left a note saying 
he had killed her in a domestic dispute 
the shaken jury was given a day to recover then started 
deliberations in the yearold trial over again defense attorneys 
asked the judge to question them about their emotional reactions to 
the murder but superior court judge michael tynan refused 
defense lawyers said jurors might be prejudiced by the fact that 
ms singletarys murder was similar to some of the crimes with which 
richard ramirez is charged 
ramirez a 29yearold drifter from el paso texas is accused of 
a series of gruesome murders and assaults that terrified los angeles 
in the summer of 1985 
the prosecution claims ramirez is the devilworshiping night 
stalker who left symbols of demon worship at some murder scenes 
and gouged out one victims eyes 
ramirez defense team argued during his trial that witnesses were 
too traumatized to make positive identifications of their assailant 
