the law effective jan 1 lowers the bloodalcohol level at 
which a person is presumed too drunk to drive from 010 percent to 
008 percent current law allows for prosecution when a drivers 
bloodalcohol level is below 010 percent if there is other evidence 
the driver was too intoxicated to drive safely convictions are 
rare however 
the new law still allows for prosecutions at levels below 008 
percent if other evidence warrants it the american medical 
association supports a 005 percent level 
a variety of factors including weight affect the amount of 
alcohol a person can consume before getting drunk the average 
person can consume about three glasses of beer or comparable amounts 
of other alcoholic beverages in an hour before reaching the 008 
percent level 
drunken drivers should beware of the lowered standard deukmejian 
said 
