here are the dates of key events in the furor over 
the satanic verses 
sept 26 1988 viking penguin publishes the satanic verses 
in london 
oct 5 india bans the book as offensive to islam the first 
country to do so 
jan 14 1989 moslems publicly burn the book in bradford 
northern england 
feb 1213 seven people are killed in antirushdie rioting in 
pakistan and india 
feb 14 ayatollah ruhollah khomeini of iran calls on moslems to 
kill rushdie and his publishers on grounds they insulted islam 
rushdie and his wife marianne wiggins go into hiding 
feb 15 protesters stone the british embassy in tehran irans 
capital an iranian cleric puts a price on rushdies head 
feb 17 president ali khamenei of iran suggests rushdie could 
be pardoned if he repents 
feb 18 rushdie apologizes for causing distress to moslems 
khomeini renews the death sentence saying the statement falls short 
of a public repentance 
feb 21 the 12nation european economic community withdraws its 
envoys from iran all but britains return within weeks 
march 7 britain and iran sever diplomatic relations 
