take an encylcopedia to bed 
it says something too about the eightpound threeounce 
encyclopedia of southern culture that not many people except for the 
citizens of fort worth texas have found much that was left out 
fort worth complains because it didnt get an entry of its own 
making it appear perhaps less southern than dallas or new orleans 
this massive and ambitious 50 1600page compendium of the 
cultural landscape of the south exploring everything from johnny 
cash to moon pies was published this summer 
even before it came out the fort worth startelegram carried a 
piece offering a carload of mint juleps if the book would just 
include fort worth 
it was a very attractive offer says ferris son of a soybean 
farmer now director of the center for the study of southern culture 
