<TEXT>
dean a mcgee one of the founders of the 
kerrmcgee corp died friday at baptist medical center hospital 
officials said 
he was 85 the cause of death was not disclosed 
mcgee was a pioneer in the offshore oil drilling industry that 
helped elevate kerrmcgee to a fortune 500 company he and the late 
sen robert s kerr were founders of the company that bears their 
names 
mcgee was vice president of kerrmcgee oil industries inc when 
he backed a plan to construct the nations first offshore oil 
derrick and platform 10 miles into the gulf of mexico in 1947 
oil began to flow from that first well nov 15 1947 it was 
plugged in 1984 after producing 14 million barrels of crude and 307 
million cubic feet of natural gas 
it didnt take long for other companies to get out there 
mcgee said in a 1987 interview 
mcgee became president and chief executive officer of kerrmcgee 
in 1954 and became chairman in 1963 he retired as chairman and 
chief executive officer in may 1983 he then became chairman 
emeritus of the executive committee 
mcgee continued to be active serving as treasurer last year of 
the initiative petition drive to limit the length of legislative 
sessions 
mcgee was born in humboldt kan 
services are scheduled monday at westminster presbyterian church 
in oklahoma city 
